Custom bindings are where SwiftUI starts to feel **really powerful** 🔥 — this is a **mid → senior level concept**.

---

# 🧠 What is a Custom Binding?

A **custom `Binding`** lets you control:

* how a value is **read**
* how a value is **written**

Instead of just doing:

```swift
TextField("Username", text: $username)
```

You can define your own logic using:

```swift
Binding(
    get: { ... },
    set: { ... }
)
```

---

# ⚙️ Syntax

```swift
Binding<T>(
    get: { value },
    set: { newValue in
        // modify / validate / transform
    }
)
```

---

# 🔥 Example 1: Trim Spaces Automatically

```swift
@State private var username = ""

var body: some View {
    TextField(
        "Username",
        text: Binding(
            get: { username },
            set: { newValue in
                username = newValue.trimmingCharacters(in: .whitespaces)
            }
        )
    )
}
```

### ✅ What happens:

* User types `"  john  "`
* Stored value becomes `"john"`

👉 You just added **input sanitization at UI level**

---

# 🔥 Example 2: Uppercase Transformation

```swift
TextField(
    "Username",
    text: Binding(
        get: { username },
        set: { username = $0.uppercased() }
    )
)
```

👉 Input automatically becomes:

```
john → JOHN
```

---

# 🔥 Example 3: Validation While Typing

```swift
@State private var password = ""
@State private var error: String?

var body: some View {
    TextField(
        "Password",
        text: Binding(
            get: { password },
            set: { newValue in
                password = newValue
                
                if newValue.count < 6 {
                    error = "Too short"
                } else {
                    error = nil
                }
            }
        )
    )
}
```

👉 You’re doing **real-time validation**

---

# 🔥 Example 4: Optional → Non-Optional Binding

Very common in production 👇

```swift
@State private var name: String? = nil

var body: some View {
    TextField(
        "Name",
        text: Binding(
            get: { name ?? "" },
            set: { name = $0 }
        )
    )
}
```

👉 Converts:

* `String?` → `String` (required by TextField)

---

# 🔥 Example 5: Derived State (Advanced ⚡)

```swift
@State private var isOn = false

var body: some View {
    Toggle(
        "Toggle",
        isOn: Binding(
            get: { isOn },
            set: { newValue in
                print("Changed to \(newValue)")
                isOn = newValue
            }
        )
    )
}
```

👉 Add logging, analytics, side effects

